message.content: cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. The paper discusses text mining methods for software engineering tasks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper specifically focuses on using LDA (Latent Dirichlet Allocation) and FFTs (Fast and Frugal Trees) for text classification, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and machine learning (ML) algorithms. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for analyzing software bug reports, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of human-comprehensible models, which involves explainable AI (XAI) techniques and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
